description: Secretary of State Antony Blinken reacted to the death of Hezbollah leader Hassan Nasrallah by saying the Middle East was safer without him and that diplomacy would continue to stabilize the region.
title: Blinken reacts to Hezbollah leaders death, says world is ‘safer without him’

description: Displaced people fleeing Israeli airstrikes in southern Lebanon have taken refuge in a parking lot in the coastal town of Sidon. Lebanon's prime minister said as many as one million people have been displaced by escalating tensions between Israel and Hezbollah.
title: Displaced people fleeing southern Lebanon take shelter in parking lot

description: A SpaceX crew is on a rescue mission to bring back two stranded astronauts, Butch Wilmore and Sunita Williams, from the International Space Station. Both astronauts were supposed to be there for eight days, but were stranded when their capsule suffered helium leaks and thruster issues. Wilmore and Williams will hitch a ride back to Earth with the SpaceX rescue team, scheduled for February 2025.
title: SpaceX rescue capsule docks at the International Space Station

description: An apparent Israeli airstrike hit an apartment building in central Beirut as Israel claims to have killed another senior Hezbollah figure just days after the assassination of their leader, Hassan Nasrallah. NBC News' Matt Bradley reports on the escalating conflict in the Middle East.
title: Israel strikes central Beirut as displaced families sleep on streets

description: Austria's Freedom Party secured the country's first far-right national parliamentary election victory since World War II, finishing ahead of the governing conservatives after tapping into anxieties about immigration, Ukraine and the economy.
title: Far-right Freedom Party wins Austrian election in an apparent boost for Putin

description: Palestinian militant group the Popular Front for the Liberation of Palestine said early Monday that three of its members were killed in a strike on a residential building in central Beirut. NBC News' Richard Engel reports from the scene, which had been regarded as a safe area in the Lebanese capital.
title: Israel launches deadly strike in central Beirut marking a fresh escalation in bombing campaign

description: Japan’s incoming prime minister, Shigeru Ishiba, said he will call a general election for Oct. 27 after winning one of the closest-ever leadership races for the governing Liberal Democratic Party.
title: Japan’s incoming leader calls general election as he seeks to unify party

description: Two weeks of public testimony concluded Friday in the U.S. Coast Guard's investigation to establish what caused the Titan submersible to implode during a deep ocean dive last year.
title: Key revelations emerge in Coast Guard's Titan submersible hearing
